Description:

The main objective of this phase is to clearly identify and understand the business problem addressed by the OptiCrop Smart Agricultural Production Optimization System. The project focuses on solving challenges faced in modern agriculture, including poor crop selection, inefficient utilization of resources, changing environmental conditions, and reduced farming productivity. Farmers often find it difficult to determine the most suitable crop based on soil nutrients and climatic conditions, which can result in low crop yield and financial losses.
This phase involves analyzing the agricultural domain and identifying the key environmental and soil parameters that influence crop growth and productivity. Important factors such as Nitrogen (N), Phosphorus (P), Potassium (K), temperature, humidity, pH value, rainfall, and seasonal conditions are studied to understand their impact on crop recommendation and agricultural optimization.
The system provides an intelligent and data-driven solution that assists farmers, agricultural researchers, agribusiness organizations, and policymakers in making informed farming decisions. By integrating Machine Learning techniques and predictive analytics, the platform recommends the most suitable crops based on environmental and soil conditions, thereby improving agricultural efficiency, sustainability, and productivity.
This phase also focuses on understanding the practical applications, business requirements, user needs, and expected outcomes of the system. The insights gathered during this stage serve as the foundation for data collection, data preprocessing, machine learning model development, application design, testing, and deployment of the crop recommendation system.
